==English==
===Etymology===
F. [[avertir]], formerly also spelt [[advertir]], to warn, give notice to, L. [[advertere]] to turn to. The ending was probably influenced by the noun [[advertisement]].  See [[Advert]].

===Pronunciation===
IPA: [[WEAE]] /ˈæd.vɚ.taɪz/

===Transitive Verb===
# To give public notice of; to announce publicly, esp. by a printed notice; as, to advertise goods for sale, a lost article, the sailing day of a vessel, a political meeting.



====Synonyms====
To [[apprise]]; [[inform]]; make known; [[notify]]; [[announce]]; [[proclaim]]; [[promulgate]]; [[publish]].

